definitions.definition: To join (to another object): to attach , or to be intended to attach or capable of attaching, to another object.
examples: I think this piece connects to that piece over there.

definitions.definition: To join : to attach , or to be intended to attach or capable of attaching, to each other.
examples: Both roads have the same name, but they don't connect : they're on opposite sides of the river, and there's no bridge there.

definitions.definition: To arrive at an intended target; to land .
examples: When that roundhouse kick connected with his temple it sent him flying across the room.

definitions.definition: To join (two other objects), or to join (one object) to (another object): to be a link between two objects, thereby attaching them to each other.
examples: The new railroad will connect the northern part of the state to the southern part.

definitions.definition: To join (two other objects), or to join (one object) to (another object): to take one object and attach it to another.
examples: I connected the printer to the computer, but I couldn't get it work.

definitions.definition: To join an electrical or telephone line to a circuit or network .
examples: When the technician connects my house, I'll be able to access the internet.

definitions.definition: To associate ; to establish a relation between.
examples: I didn't connect my lost jewelry with the news of an area cat burglar until the police contacted me.

definitions.definition: To make a travel connection ; to switch from one means of transport to another as part of the same trip.
examples: I'm flying to London where I connect with a flight heading to Hungary.

main_definition: ( intransitive , of an object ) To join (to another object): to attach , or to be intended to attach or capable of attaching, to another object.
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive , of two objects ) To join : to attach , or to be intended to attach or capable of attaching, to each other.
( intransitive , of a blow ) To arrive at an intended target; to land .
